Mikki Nicholson stepped in front of a train after suffering verbal abuse in Carlisle . 
  She was a national Scrabble champion and had planned a move to Newcastle . 
  But she changed her mind after being told she risked homelessness if she left her social housing . 
  The 36-year-old was born male but identified as a woman . 
  Inquest heard she suffered daily verbal abuse and planned to move . 
  Ms Nicholson died on November 7 last year after being taunted in the street . 
 